-- South African Coal Export Prices Rise for First Time in 11 Weeks
-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 2012-06-25T14:43:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-25/south-african-coal-export-prices-rise-for-first-time-in-11-weeks.html
Coal export prices at  South Africa ’s
 Richards Bay , the continent’s biggest terminal for shipping the
fuel, increased for the first time in 11 weeks.  Prices added $1.97, or 2.4 percent, to $83.89 a metric ton
in the week ended June 22, according to IHS McCloskey data on
Bloomberg. That’s the first gain since the week ended April 6.
The price is quoted on a free-on-board basis, which excludes
delivery costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
